  "body": "As far as I investigated `go-etheretum` supports the following `content-types` in HTTP based JSON-RPC requests ([referred code](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/59a48e0289b1a7470a8285e665cab12b29117a70/rpc/http.go#L41)) \r\n- application/json\r\n- application/json-rpc\r\n- application/jsonrequest\r\n\r\n `ethers-io/erhers.js` seems to add support for `text/plain` `content-type` with its new version 6. Related code line https://github.com/ethers-io/ethers.js/blob/v6/src.ts/utils/fetch.ts#L221. When I run client test with the `ethers` v6_beta, I receive `Error: server response 415 Unsupported Media Type`. \r\n\r\nWhen `text/plain` added to [acceptedContentTypes](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/59a48e0289b1a7470a8285e665cab12b29117a70/rpc/http.go#L41) slice, the issue is resolved.\r\n\r\nMy question is  -> Is this a reasonable change for go-ethereum ecosystem to support other client libraries? \r\n\r\n\r\nTest code to reproduce the issue. \r\nPlease first install the ethers v6_beta version.\r\n`npm install ethers@6.0.0-beta-exports.10`\r\n \r\nThen, set the environment/url and run a simple request. \r\n\r\n\r\n`import { ethers } from 'ethers'`\r\n`  (async () => {`\r\n`    const provider = new ethers.JsonRpcProvider(env)`\r\n`    const block = await provider.getBlock('latest')`\r\n`    console.log('block', block)`\r\n`  })();`",
