    "body": "This has [already been fixed](https://github.com/ethers-io/ethers.js/commit/e55a87ad4c355743fd68c88e21e92d46b1c92694) in the v6 beta branch. It was a consequence of how the new FetchRequest works and how it was used, but it was definitely a bug.\r\n\r\nI don’t think it makes too sense to add, as it is easy for clients to “do the right thing”. The only reason I sometimes wish it was more flexible is when using curl, but this seems like a fairly weak reason. :)",
